    "\n",
    "### Marginalia (`.column-margin`)\n",
    "\n",
    "The next paragraph has a margin note attached to it. On screens wider than ~1100px the note appears in the right-hand margin; on narrower screens it falls below the paragraph. In the PDF (Typst) build the same content appears as a Tufte-style sidenote on the outer edge of the page.\n",
    "\n",
    "This is body text. The margin note is the subject of much of this project's design intent — it lets the author put parenthetical commentary, references, definitional asides, and pedagogical scaffolding *next to* the line of argument it qualifies, rather than below it as a footnote or buried inside parentheses.\n",
    "\n",
    "::: {.column-margin}\n",
    "This is a margin note. Use `:::{.column-margin}` blocks for editorial asides — short context, references, \"see also Chapter X\" pointers. Long technical sidebars belong in callout boxes inline.\n",
    ":::\n",
    "\n",
    "### Footnotes pushed to the margin\n",
    "\n",
    "The Quarto book is configured with `reference-location: margin`, so a footnote like this one[^demo-fn] renders as a sidenote in HTML and a Tufte-style sidenote in PDF.\n",
