    "### An Observable widget (OJS)\n",
    "\n",
    "The next block is an Observable JS slider tied to a simple plot. It demonstrates the OJS embedding pattern for inline interactive widgets — the kind that drag-a-slider-watch-the-curve-move pedagogy benefits from.\n",
    "\n",
    "```{ojs}\n",
    "//| label: fig-demo-ojs\n",
    "\n",
    "viewof alpha_demo = Inputs.range([0.05, 0.95], {value: 0.4, step: 0.05, label: \"Cobb-Douglas α\"})\n",
    "\n",
    "curve_demo = {\n",
    "  const xs = d3.range(0.1, 10, 0.1);\n",
    "  const ys = xs.map(x => Math.pow(x, alpha_demo) * Math.pow(5, 1 - alpha_demo));\n",
    "  return Plot.plot({\n",
    "    width: 600,\n",
    "    height: 300,\n",
    "    x: { label: \"x\" },\n",
    "    y: { label: \"u(x, 5)\" },\n",
    "    marks: [\n",
    "      Plot.line(xs.map((x, i) => ({x, y: ys[i]})), { x: \"x\", y: \"y\", stroke: \"steelblue\" })\n",
    "    ]\n",
    "  });\n",
    "}\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "### A JSXGraph widget\n",
    "\n",
    "JSXGraph is the project's primary tool for inline math interactives — \"type a function, drag a slider, see a curve respond.\" The block below is a slider-controlled function plot, embedded as raw HTML so it works whether or not the `jsxgraph/jsxgraph-quarto` extension has been installed yet (see PRD Addendum 1 §1.5; once installed, prefer the extension's shortcode). The JSXGraph runtime is loaded globally via `include-in-header` in `_quarto.yml`.\n",
    "\n",
    "```{=html}\n",
    "<div id=\"jxg-demo-index\" class=\"jxgbox\" style=\"width: 600px; height: 400px;\"></div>\n",
    "<script>\n",
    "(function() {\n",
    "  const board = JXG.JSXGraph.initBoard(\"jxg-demo-index\", {\n",
    "    boundingbox: [-0.5, 12, 11, -1],\n",
    "    axis: true,\n",
    "    showCopyright: false,\n",
    "    showNavigation: false\n",
    "  });\n",
    "  const alpha = board.create(\"slider\",\n",
    "    [[1, 10], [9, 10], [0.05, 0.4, 0.95]],\n",
    "    { name: \"&#945;\", snapWidth: 0.05 });\n",
    "  board.create(\"functiongraph\",\n",
    "    [function(x) { return Math.pow(x, alpha.Value()); }, 0.01, 10],\n",
    "    { strokeColor: \"steelblue\", strokeWidth: 2 });\n",
    "})();\n",
    "</script>\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "JSXGraph widgets render only in HTML; the PDF build skips them. For chapters with critical JSXGraph content, ship a static SVG fallback (see `assets/scripts/render-jsxgraph-fallback.py`, currently a stub).\n",
